  <body>
    <p id="p_ox2_dgk_54b">In <ph keyref="product"/>, a <term>plugin</term> can be packed and deployed as an
        <term>add-on</term> to provide additional functionality to the application.</p>
    <section id="packing_a_plugin_or_framework_as_an_addon">
      <title>Packing a Plugin as an Add-on</title>
      <p id="p_px2_dgk_54b">This procedure is suitable for developers who want a better control over the <xref
          keyref="glossentry_plugin"><term>add-on</term></xref> package or those who want to
        automate some of the steps:<ol id="ol_qx2_dgk_54b">
          <li id="li_rx2_dgk_54b">Pack the <xref keyref="glossentry_plugin"><term>plugin</term></xref> as a ZIP file or
            a <xref keyref="glossentry_jar"><term>Java Archive</term></xref>. Note that you should
            pack the entire root directory not just its contents.</li>
          <li conkeyref="reusables-tools/li2" id="li_sx2_dgk_54b"/>
          <li conkeyref="reusables-tools/li3" id="li_tx2_dgk_54b"/>
        </ol></p>
    </section>
